03599nam a22005535i 9780822384991DE-B159720220729113935.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220729t20032003ncu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808223849917 a10.1515/97808223849912doi  a(DE-B1597)553272  a(OCoLC)1055305863  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ancucUS-NC 7aLIT0000002bisacsh1 aGreen, Anna Katharine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aThat Affair Next Door and Lost Man's Lane /cAnna Katharine Green. 1aDurham : bDuke University Press, c[2003] 4c©2003  a1 online resource (452 p.) :b2 line drawings  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tIntroduction -- tThat Affair Next Door -- tLost Man’s Lane: A Second Episode in the Life of Amelia Butterworth0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAnna Katharine Green was the most famous and prolific writer of detective fiction in the United States prior to Dashiell Hammett. Her first novel, The Leavenworth Case, was the bestseller of 1878. Green is credited with a number of “firsts” within the mystery genre, including the gentleman murdered as he makes out his will and the icicle as murder weapon. She created the first female detectives in American fiction. Her amateur spinster sleuth, Amelia Butterworth, became the prototype for numerous women detectives to follow, including Agatha Christie’s Miss Marple. Nosy, opinionated, and tenacious, Amelia Butterworth engages in a sustained rivalry with Ebenezer Gryce, a police detective. In the interaction between these characters, Green developed two more conventions adopted by future generations of mystery writers: the investigation as battle between the sexes and between the professional and the unexpectedly sharp, observant amateur. This volume presents two of Green’s Amelia Butterworth tales: That Affair Next Door (1897) and Lost Man’s Lane (1898).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aDetective and mystery stories, American. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aGreen, Anna Katharine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNickerson, Catherine Ross, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoss Nickerson, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107118370 cprintz978082233153740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822384991?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822384991423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822384991/original  a978-3-11-071183-7  Duke University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles